# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/core

### Is this a regression?
Possibly
### Description
When two directives can set the same attribute, it will result in an error during debug pass.

While debugging I have found, that values are set as one would expect.

SRC is set from getSrcDirective, then received in FallbackDirective and saved as `originalSrc`, then it will do a debug pass. 

In debug pass image src is set to null, that will result in an error and the error will ask for fallback.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-pvqy4g

HTML
```lang-html
<div>
	<h3>Both</h3>
	<img
		sGetSrc="//via.placeholder.com/120x60?text=Good"
		sFallback="//via.placeholder.com/120x60?text=Fallback"
	>
</div>
```

GetSrcDirective [sGetSrc]
```lang-ts
export class GetSrcDirective {
	@HostBinding('src') @Input('sGetSrc') image!: string;
}
```

FallbackDirective[sFallback]
```lang-ts
export class FallbackDirective {
	@HostBinding('class.no-image') hasError = false;

	private originalSrc!: string;
	@Input('src') set src(value: string) {
		if (!value) { return; }
		if (value == this.originalSrc) { return; }

		this.hasError = false;
		this.originalSrc = value;
	}
	@Input() sFallback!: string;

	@HostBinding('src') get currentSrc(): string {
		if (this.hasError) {
			return this.sFallback;
		} else {
			return this.originalSrc;
		}
	}

	@HostListener('error')
	failure() {
		this.hasError = true;
	}
}
```

